featured_reviews.review_id:
One of the best example of islamic architecture this Makkah Masjid is situated at heart of Hyderabad city, as a masjid or mosque this place is only for prayer and to offer salah but people used this as a picnic spot which is not good.
Structure is very beautiful and and spread in a very large area and situated just in front of Char minar and market area.
There are so many hotels for food here also a very good market outside for jwellery and clothes.
It is easily accessible from railway station by bus, auto or cab but a bit far from airport.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Very beautiful and big mosque.  It is also known as Jama Masjid Shafiabad.  The splendor of this place is worth seeing during the days of Ramzan.  Here Tarawi is arranged on both the ground floor and first floor in Ramzan.  The name of the Imam here is Qasim Habibi, who has been offering Namaz in this mosque for 40 years.  There are many shops outside this mosque, in which vegetable shop, dry clean shop, barber shop, biryani shop and bike repairing shop are the main ones.  This is a very old mosque.  There is also a madrasa in this mosque where many children get education.
